title: Dieciocho
overview: Celia and Moha meet in a kitchen. For Celia, this job is a punishment: a judge has ordered her to do community service. For Moha, this job is a reward that brings her closer to her goal of getting her papers. Although it may not seem like it, they have a lot in common, and they will discover it as they both overcome their prejudices and begin to see each other as they truly are.Â
